Kowloon's color-jurisdiction system implements Amenhotep's design principle — institutional specialization with clear jurisdictional boundaries — with the addition of cross-jurisdiction accountability.
Kowloon's position: Amenhotep's design was the prototype of what Kowloon's governance implements. His version had no accountability mechanism. Kowloon's version does.

